The course presents an overview of the orthography of sounds in the Estonian Language, one word or hyphenated spellings, punctuation.Objectives/eesmärkid:  1) to teach the basic rules of the orthography of sounds, one word or hyphenated spellings, punctuation and the use of abbreviations; 2) to explan of foreign, especially Russian names, transcription and the difference from transliteration.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  1) write in Estonian according to the rules of orthography; 2) knows the orthography of sounds, the rules of capital letters, one word or hyphenated spellings, punctuation and the the use of abbreviations.
